java.lang.Object
org.mariuszgromada.math.mxparser.StringResources
public class StringResources extends Object
A class containing definition of user (interface) language. List of available languages: English, French, German, Italian, Polish, Portuguese, Spanish. Class also allows a new user language definition - for instance user defined translation. Translation can be done via extending this class.

    • print

      public void print()
      Displays user-defined text resources in the console. The default value is shown and, if the current value is different from the default value, the current value is also shown. The method can be very useful when analyzing the correctness and completeness of defined resources, especially when translating into other languages.

    • printInitSrc

      public void printInitSrc()
      Displays the initial text resource definitions as source code. The method can be very useful when creating your own text resources, as it can be used as a basis for translation.
